[SN]TITLE[SN]
Grant to repair River Severn river bank in Worcester

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A river bank damaged by flooding and storms in 2013 is to be repaired thanks to a lottery grant.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 5th Worcester Sea Scout Group has received Â£76,254 from Sport England's Flood Relief Fund.
The money will be used to restore a section of the eroded River Severn riverbank at Northwick and create a barrier to stop water getting onto the land in the future.
Group Scout Leader Robert Sidley said he was "delighted".
